30|$|The most {{important}} procedures in producing <b>neutron</b> <b>sources</b> are fission reaction in reactors and spallation phenomena in accelerator-driven systems. Spallation <b>neutron</b> <b>sources</b> {{are of interest}} for transmutation of long-lived actinides and fission products from nuclear waste [3], plutonium from nuclear weapons [4], or thorium (as an energy source) [5], used for material research and industry [6] or medicine for radiotherapy [7].|$|R
